713221f-a.title: Manhattan: 45th Street - 3rd Street
713221f-a.text:
45th Street, south side, east from 216 East 45th Street, east
of Third Avenue. No. 220-222, two frame houses built in 1854,
were formerly the home of H. J. Conway. This view was taken on
the day on which the signing of the Armistioe ended the World War.
November 11, 1918.
0ift of Miss Grace A. Conway.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
